From 0673d0d6856a0a89a9d0f62188be57322aa2cb74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dzmitry Sankouski <dsankouski@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 7 Jun 2024 17:47:31 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 177/194] ASoC: codecs: add support for MAX98512 based on
 downstream

Temporary solution, until proper driver gets into mainline!

Please, preferably do not waste time on improving except import or
security/crash bugfixes. Rather invest time into upstreaming if possible.

Imported with small adjustments:
- `{techpack/audio/asoc/codecs/max98512*,techpack/audio/asoc/codecs/maxim_dsm*} -> max98512-downstream/`
- trash Samsung dependencies
- unconditionally return error on dsm calibration file access
- small few unimportant lines of changes to compile

Imported from:
https://github.com/klabit87/android_kernel_samsung_sdm845/tree/q/techpack/audio/asoc/codecs,
adjusted using https://github.com/j0sh1x/tfa98xx as an example.

sound: soc: codecs: max98512: fix deprecated DAIFMT
